          "valueString": "https://www.rcpa.edu.au/Manuals/RCPA-Manual/Pathology-Tests/B/Blood-culture"
        },
        {
          "code": "requiredSpecimen",
          "valueString": "The volume of blood collected (min 20 mL in adults) is a critical factor in determining positivity. Aerobic and Non-aerobic culture bottles (1 set) to be collected using aseptic technique for adults; Paediatric - collect one paediatric bottle. Multiple samples from different sites can assist in detection of infection."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
